Python tools for SETI 
 blimpy (Breakthrough Listen I/O Methods for Python)
Purpose: Reading and processing large radio astronomy data files (especially .fil and .h5 formats from telescopes like GBT, Parkes, MeerKAT).


ðŸ”¹ turboSETI
Purpose: Searches for narrowband signals with Doppler drift (classic SETI technique).


ðŸ”¹ setigen
Purpose: Simulate and generate synthetic SETI signals for testing pipelines and ML models.


Other SETI & Radio Astronomy Tools

ðŸ”¹ PySETI
A Python framework for SETI signal search (alternative to turboSETI).

ðŸ”¹ SigPyRFI (Signal Processing for RFI Mitigation)
Purpose: Remove Radio Frequency Interference (RFI) from telescope data.


ðŸ”¹ Voyager (SETI Candidate Management)
A tool for managing and classifying candidate signals.



